race.description: Ckb Civil Eddie Latta Memorial Handicap (C1)
race.comment: CANDO ATTITUDE (6) wasted no time getting off the mark as favourite on debut at Moruya two-and-a-half weeks ago. Has buckets of upside and keeps winning apprentice. Can go on with the job. COMMANDORO (7) doesn't win out of turn but is knocking on the door. Performed well last time at Moruya, finishing a close second after showing good early muster. Drawn to advantage on the inside and should be in this for a long way. TRIANON (9) closed off nicely into fourth when resuming at long odds at Moruya off a long break. Better for the run and deserves more respect this time. Small field however it possesses solid depth. COMPLAISANCE (1) and NAGADEC (2) both appeal early in their campaigns.
